The paper discusses the hardware implementation of deep neural networks using stochastic computing, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the energy consumption and fault-tolerant nature of the proposed architecture, which could fall under the categories of computer engineering (cs.CE) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes an efficient implementation of a DNN, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
